The paper deals with channel coding rate in the finite block-length regime and under additive white Gaussian noise conditions, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also involves numerical evaluation methods, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. The paper's focus on evaluating the Polyanskiy Poor Verdu converse bound could also fall under statistical inference (cs.SI) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
